quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,103,"But those whose scales are light - those are the ones who have lost their souls, [being] in Hell, abiding eternally."
  23,104,"The Fire will sear their faces, and they therein will have taut smiles.{1}",footnotes:1:Their lips having been contracted by scorching until the teeth are exposed.
  23,105,"[It will be said], "
  25,49,"That We may bring to life thereby a dead land and give it as drink to those We created of numerous livestock and men."
  25,50,"And We have certainly distributed it among them that they might be reminded,{1} but most of the people refuse except disbelief.",footnotes:1:Of Allāh's ability to bring the dead to life.
  25,51,"And if We had willed, We could have sent into every city a warner.{1}",footnotes:1:However, Allāh willed that Prophet Muḥammad (ﷺ) be sent as the final messenger for all peoples of the earth until the Day of Resurrection.
  26,22,"And is this a favor of which you remind me - that you have enslaved the Children of Israel?"
  26,23,"Said Pharaoh, "
  26,24,"[Moses] said, "